    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - CRANKSHAFT
        (Reconditioning) - CRANKSHAFT FLANGE INSPECTION AND REPAIR
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
        <title>CRANKSHAFT FLANGE INSPECTION AND REPAIR</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If crankshaft flange has been previously fitted with an optional wear sleeve from Rear Oil
                Seal and Wear Sleeve Package (P/N 1 807 788 C92), remove the wear sleeve by carefully "tapping" with a
                hammer (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e435_115.xml" xrefid="ef4350632">6.32</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Be careful not to damage the crankshaft flange face or O.D.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Prior to crankshaft installation, inspect crankcase as outlined later in this section.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
